<h3>Creating the FHIR Implementation Guide</h3>

<p>Initial creation of a FHIR IG can start quite early and iterate as the model is improved. </p>

<p>FHIR Shorthand (FSH) is “a domain-specific language for defining FHIR artifacts involved in creation of FHIR Implementation Guides (IG). The goal of FSH is to allow Implementation Guide (IG) creators to more directly express their intent with fewer concerns about underlying FHIR mechanics, and efficiently produce high-quality FHIR IGs.”  FSH is an HL7 standard. FSH is increasingly used around the world, and probably on other planets.</p>

